    "description": "&quot;Live Mas.&quot;\n– Taco Bell slogan. \n\n&quot;I did what I could.&quot;\n– Edward Abbey, last words. \n\nVladimir: &quot;Come on, Gogo, return the ball, can't you, once in a way?&quot;\nEstragon: (with exaggerated enthusiasm). &quot;I find this really most extraordinarily interesting.&quot;\n– Samuel Beckett, 'Waiting for Godot' (1952) \n\n&quot;Take the birds which you'll have noticed in so many of my recent paintings. I never thought them up, they just materialized of their own accord; they were born on the canvas... it is absurd to read any sort of symbolic significance into them.&quot;\n– Georges Braque",
